Sec. 41.031. CERTIFICATION OF RESULTS. If the commissioner
finds that two-thirds or more of those voting in the election voted
in favor of the referendum proposition or that those voting in favor
of the proposition produced at least 50 percent of the volume of
production of the commodity during the relevant production period,
the commissioner shall publicly certify the adoption of the
referendum proposition and issue certificates of election to those
persons elected to the board. Otherwise, the commissioner shall
publicly certify that the referendum proposition was defeated.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1085, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

